## v2.2.0 (2026-05-04)
**Changed by:** 2026-05-04 full-corpus Myrmidon deduplication session (1,659 → 982 files, two passes)
**Verification:** verified-ci (171/171 tests passing, 982/982 plugins valid)

### What changed
- Added "Gap Recovery Second Pass" subsection to Verified Workflow (augment-not-replace approach for incomplete Wave 1 coverage)
- Added 2 new Failed Attempts rows: Explore agents for fingerprinting (read-only, cannot Write JSONL), oversized shards causing silent coverage gaps
- Added Verified On row for 2026-05-04 session (57 files absorbed across 2 passes)
- Bumped date to 2026-05-04

### Why
Gap-recovery second pass and agent-type discipline (general-purpose vs Explore) were the two critical new learnings from the largest corpus dedup run to date. Documents: ≤103-file shard ceiling, `comm -23` gap detection, cluster ID sequencing (C060+), and addendum-not-overwrite pattern for multi-pass audit trails.

